comment: Gordon (HOU) makes contact with Kilpatrick's (BKN) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Nene (HOU) beats Kilpatrick (BKN) to the spot and obtains a legal guarding position at the time of the contact.
Lopez (BKN) maintains legal guarding position and makes contact with the ball on the driving shot attempt by Harden (HOU).
Harden (HOU) makes marginal contact with Kilpatrick (BKN) on the perimeter prior to receiving the pass.
Lopez (BKN) legally contests Harden's (HOU) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Nene (HOU) dislodges the ball from Lopez (BKN) without affecting his SQBR. The two players then briefly engage and separate.
Harden (HOU) makes marginal contact with Kilpatrick (BKN) on his move prior to the shot attempt.
Lopez (BKN) legally contests Harden's (HOU) jump shot attempt and allows him to land. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Ariza (HOU) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by Harris (BKN) and then makes contact with the ball.
Harden (HOU) does not dislodge Kilpatrick (BKN) from his legal guarding position on the perimeter.
Lin (BKN) makes contact with Nene's (HOU) arm that affects his ability to control the pass.
Ariza (HOU) makes contact with the ball and cleanly blocks Harris' (BKN) shot attempt.
Kilpatrick (BKN) commits a take foul on Gordon (HOU).

[Observable in enhanced video] RHH shows that Lin (BKN) gathers the ball into Nene's (HOU) knee, but he then makes contact with the ball once more prior to it going OOB. The call on the floor was Brooklyn ball and officials did not go to replay review.
[Detectable with stop watch] Brooklyn does not inbound the ball within 5 seconds.
Nene (HOU) and Lopez (BKN) briefly engage and separate during the inbound.
Beverley (HOU) grabs and holds Lin (BKN) and affects his FOM during the inbound.
Lopez (BKN) commits a take foul on Gordon (HOU).
Nene (HOU) and Lopez (BKN) briefly engage and separate just prior to Lopez receiving the inbound pass.
